    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nThere is no reason for `nvim_get_option_value` and `nvim_get_option_info2` to be separate APIs.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nIntroduce `nvim_option_get`.\r\nDeprecate `nvim_get_option_value` and `nvim_get_option_info2`.\r\n\r\ntodo\r\n\r\n- [ ] benchmark\r\n- [ ] tests\r\n- [ ] replace old references\r\n- [ ] docs + news\r\n- [ ] cleanup implementation",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'm not really a fan of APIs with polymorphic return types as it makes it difficult/impossible to add accurate type annotations. Can we reconsider this?\n\n>There is no reason for nvim_get_option_value and nvim_get_option_info2 to be separate APIs.\n\nGetting an option value will now incur the cost of a dictionary and a table allocation, along with fetching all the option info which is seldom used compared to the value.",
